    "ai-tha-ap533:25.4_0": "and live without defilements.",
    "ai-tha-ap533:26.1_0": "It was truly for me",
    "ai-tha-ap533:26.2_0": "to me like the Buddha.",
    "ai-tha-ap533:26.3_0": "I attained the three knowledges",
    "ai-tha-ap533:26.4_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "ai-tha-ap533:27.1_0": "Attaining the four kinds of textual analysis",
    "ai-tha-ap533:27.2_0": "and skeleton without flesh or blood,",
    "ai-tha-ap533:27.3_0": "I have realized the six kinds of direct knowledge,",
    "ai-tha-ap533:27.4_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "ai-tha-ap533:28.1_0": "That is how these verses were recited by the senior venerable Mahākaccāyana.",
    "ai-tha-ap533:29.1_0": "The senior monk Pahākaccāyana first."
